                        <condition key="deficient">The sewing is partly missing; almost all quires are unbound. The back board is broken and has been repaired with a thread of plastic and metal wire.&#xD;
The Ms. shows traces of intensive use.&#xD;
Many leaves are badly stained with wax and dirt (e.g., <locus target="20v">20v</locus>, 26r, 31r, 51r-v).&#xD;
Text is barely legible or illegible on some leaves, e.g., <locus target="27r">27r</locus>, 54v, 57ra, 75ra.&#xD;
The Ms. is damaged by rodents in the bottom margin of fols. 1-10; by fire, e.g., on <locus target="32">32</locus>, 38, 53, 78, with loss of text.&#xD;
Remains of glues are preserved on the inner side of left board.&#xD;
<locus target="131">131</locus> is a leaf of different size originating from another (somewhat older) Ms.&#xD;
Tears amended on <locus target="95">95</locus>, 121.</condition>
