                  <additions><!--THIS element in domlib CONTAINS ESCAPED HTML, thus it is not possible to reliably extract the information about pages. Please watch out.-->
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#45rb">f. 45rb</locus>
                           <desc>: Donation note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="45rb">45rb</locus>: ወልደ፡ ሐዋርያት፡ ወብእሲቱ፡ ወለተ፡ ሩፋኤል፡ ውሉዱ፡ መንበረ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ዘወሀበቶ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ቤት፡ መኳዕ፡ በሲመቱ፡ ፆተ፡ ሥላሴ።</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note>
                           The note is written in deep brown ink and states that Mänbärä Śǝllāse donated this book to Mikāʾel Bet Mäkwaʿ during the tenure of Ṣotä Śǝllāse. Her father Walda Ḥawāryāt and her mother Walatta Rufāʾel are also mentioned.
                        </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#45rb">f. 45rb</locus>
                           <desc>: Donation note. </desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="45rb">45rb</locus>: ዝ፡ መጽሀፈ፡ ቅዳሴ፡ ዘቅዱስ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ቤት፡ ሙኵዕ፡ ዘወሐቦ፡ መንበረ፡ ሥላሴ፡ በሲመቱ፡ ለጾታ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ወጻፌ፡ ዝንቱ፡ ገብረ፡ ትወይሕ። …</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note>
                           The note is crudely written in dark grey ink and states that Mänbärä Śǝllāse donated this book to Mikāʾel Bet Mukwǝʿ during the tenure of Ṣotä Śǝllāse.
                        </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#129va">f. 129va</locus>
                           <desc>: Donation note. </desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="129va">129va</locus>: ዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ ቅዳሴ፡ ዘቅዱስ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ቤት፡ መኳዕ፡ ዘወሀበቶ፡ መንበረ፡ ሥላሴ፡ በሲመተ፡ ፆታ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ወምስለ፡ ኵሎሙ፡ ደቂቀ፡ ማኅበረ፡ ካህናት፡ ወዲያቆናት፡ ኀቡረ፡ ይምህሮሙ፡ ወይሠሃሎሙ፡ መንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት። </quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note>
                           The note is written in deep brown ink, possibly in the same hand as Additio 1. It states that Mänbärä Śǝllāse donated this book to Mikāʾel Bet Mäkwaʿ during the tenure of Ṣotä Śǝllāse.
                        </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Texts I, II, III contain musical notation signs.&#xD;
- Tamallas-sign, in the shape of two perpendicular lines (┴), indicating the place where the omissions, written in the upper margin, belong: <locus target="8rb">8rb</locus>, 87vb, 126ra, 128ra.&#xD;
- Omitted letters or words inserted interlineally: e.g., <locus target="16vb">16vb</locus>, 26rb, 62va, 65ra, 68va.&#xD;
- Omitted words added at the end of the line in small script: <locus target="62va">62va</locus>, 124rb.&#xD;
- Immediate corrections indicated by series of dashes above and below the letters or the words: <locus target="13ra">13ra</locus>, 22va, 83va, 89ra, 124rb.&#xD;
- Corrections indicated by two lines in black ink over the word: <locus target="10rb">10rb</locus>, 59ra, 98va.&#xD;
- Lacunae (spaces for names left unfilled) on many leaves: e.g., <locus target="7vb">7vb</locus>, 14vb, 30va, 41vb, 59rb, 95va.&#xD;
- Numbers are written in red ink in the left margin of <locus target="6va">6va</locus>, 7ra (here also in the intercolumn), 74ra (here also in black ink), 85va (here also in black ink).&#xD;
 - Pen trial: <locus target="1r">1r</locus>, 1v, 132r.&#xD;
- Scribbles: <locus target="3r">3r</locus>, 9ra, 33va, 69v, 130r.&#xD;
- Prayers and other minor texts are crudely written in dark grey ink, possibly in the same hand as Additio 2, on <locus target="2r">2r</locus>, 2vb (here effaced), 129v, 130r, 130v, 132r, 132v. One of the prayers on <locus target="129vb">129vb</locus> mentions the date 1903 year of mercy (= 1911 AD).&#xD;
- A prayer with musical notation signs is written, possibly in the main hand, on <locus target="2va">2va</locus>.&#xD;
- <locus target="131">131</locus> originates from a Maṣḥafa Täklil “Book of the Marriage Ritual”.&#xD;
- Note almost illegible in deep brown ink on <locus target="55vb">55vb</locus>.</item>
                     </list>
